title: For Sale:  RAS-47 with drum
postcontent: My loss will be your gain. First I want to say this rifle functions as it should. It looks very nice with no wear, No jams, every round goes bang and it's as accurate as any ak. With the AK goes 4 tapco mags and a brand new unused 75 round Romanian drum I just paid 100.00 for. However There are two reasons why I have it priced so low and I want anyone interested to know everything about the rifle so we have a fair transaction with no uncertainty. I did not know when I bought this AK that the previous owner did some gun smithing on it to install the Zukarov hand guard on it. When I paid 45.00 for another handguard I can't now return I figured out that the retaining ring to keep most handguards on is no longer there. And the sling loop had been dremmled off to install the handguard. Also one of the screws on the handguard won't go back in because the threading is stripped in the handguard. Nevertheless the handguard is firm and secure. The second is very minor... After shooting about 200 rounds through the rifle the stock needs to be tightened. There are plenty of different stock options for the rifle as well as a few handguards but I'm calling it quits on this one because it is my only rifle. This would be a great inexpensive AK for someone that patiently can work on them or someone that doesn't care about these two issues. If interested text REDACTED 550.00 OBO thanks!
